(41, 5, 21, 41, 4, 1, 1, 'much people gathered unto him', 'Gathering by the Sea', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of a great multitude by the sea, illustrating the significance of this location in Jesus'' ministry. The transition from teaching to healing highlights the continuity of Jesus'' interactions with the people.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 21, 42, 8, 40, 40, 'much people gathered unto him', 'Jesus'' Return and Reception', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' return to the people, highlighting their eagerness to receive him. The gathering of the crowd in Mark parallels the glad reception in Luke, indicating a shared theme of anticipation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 42, 13, 14, 14, NULL, 'Authority of Synagogue Rulers', 'This connection highlights the role of synagogue rulers in both passages. Jairus, as a ruler, seeks Jesus'' help, while another ruler expresses indignation at Jesus'' actions, showcasing the tension between authority and Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 41, 5, 35, 36, NULL, 'Fear and Faith in Crisis', 'Both passages emphasize the ruler''s desperate situation regarding his daughter. The transition from Jairus''s plea to the news of his daughter''s death highlights the theme of fear and the call to faith in Jesus''s response.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 44, 13, 15, 15, 'rulers of the synagogue', 'Rulers of the Synagogue', 'This connection highlights the role of synagogue rulers in both passages. Jairus, a ruler, approaches Jesus, while in Acts, rulers invite exhortation, showing their leadership in spiritual matters.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 44, 18, 8, 8, 'rulers of the synagogue', 'Rulers of the Synagogue', 'This connection highlights the role of synagogue leaders in both passages. Jairus, a ruler, seeks Jesus, while Crispus, the chief ruler, believes in Him.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 40, 9, 18, 26, 'fell at his feet', 'Healing of Jairus'' Daughter', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a ruler who seeks Jesus to heal his daughter. The act of falling at Jesus'' feet in Mark parallels the ruler worshipping Jesus in Matthew, highlighting their desperation and faith.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 42, 5, 8, 8, 'fell at his feet', 'Responses to Jesus'' Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility in the presence of Jesus. Both Jairus and Simon Peter demonstrate reverence by falling at Jesus'' feet or knees, acknowledging His authority and their own unworthiness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 22, 40, 2, 11, 11, 'fell at his feet', 'Worship and Humility', 'This connection highlights the act of falling down in reverence. Both Jairus and the Magi demonstrate humility by falling at the feet of Jesus, indicating a recognition of his authority and significance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 42, 13, 13, 13, 'lay thy hands on her', 'Healing through Laying on Hands', 'This connection highlights the act of laying hands for healing. Both passages emphasize the immediate healing that occurs when hands are laid on the afflicted.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 41, 16, 18, 18, 'lay thy hands on her', 'Healing Through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands on the sick as a means of healing. In Mark 5:23, the request is made for healing through laying on hands, while Mark 16:18 affirms that this practice leads to recovery.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 42, 4, 40, 40, 'lay thy hands on her', 'Healing Through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands for healing. In Mark, the request is made for Jesus to lay hands on a dying girl, while in Luke, Jesus lays hands on many sick individuals to heal them.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 44, 28, 8, 8, 'lay thy hands on her', 'Healing Through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands for healing. In Mark, Jesus is asked to lay hands on a dying girl, while in Acts, Paul lays hands on Publius to heal him. This connection highlights a consistent theme of healing through the physical act of laying on hands.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 10, 12, 15, 16, 'besought him greatly', 'Healing and Intercession', 'Both passages emphasize the act of beseeching for healing. In Mark, a father pleads for his dying daughter, while in 2 Samuel, David beseeches God for his sick child. This connection highlights the theme of desperate prayer for the health of a child.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 12, 5, 11, 11, 'lay thy hands on her', 'Healing through Touch', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing through physical touch. In both passages, the act of laying hands is central to the healing process, emphasizing the expectation of recovery through direct interaction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 23, 19, 50, 15, 15, 'I pray thee, come and lay thy hands on her', 'Healing and Deliverance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of calling upon God in times of distress. In both passages, there is a plea for healing and deliverance, emphasizing faith in God''s ability to save.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 24, 41, 5, 31, 31, 'much people followed him, and thronged him', 'Thronging Multitude Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the crowd''s presence around Jesus, highlighting the overwhelming nature of the throng. The disciples'' reference to the multitude in the second passage connects directly to the earlier description of the crowd following Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 24, 41, 3, 9, 10, 'thronged him', 'Crowds Pressing Upon Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the large crowds that followed Jesus, leading to situations where he needed to be protected from being thronged. The mention of people pressing upon him in Mark 3:10 parallels the thronging described in Mark 5:24.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 24, 42, 7, 6, 6, 'Jesus went with him', 'Jesus'' Journey to Heal', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movement towards healing. In Mark, Jesus goes with a man, while in Luke, he is approached by friends of a centurion, indicating his willingness to respond to requests for help.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 24, 42, 8, 42, 42, NULL, 'Crowd Following Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the thronging of people around Jesus as he travels to heal a dying girl. This connection highlights the urgency and desperation of the crowd in seeking Jesus'' help.', 'parallel', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 24, 44, 10, 38, 38, NULL, 'Jesus'' Healing Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' active role in healing and doing good. Mark highlights the crowds following him, while Acts describes his anointing and power to heal the oppressed.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 3, 15, 25, 27, 'issue of blood twelve years', 'Connection of Uncleanness and Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of uncleanness associated with blood issues. The woman in Mark 5:25 suffers from an issue of blood for twelve years, paralleling the regulations in Leviticus 15:25-27 regarding a woman''s uncleanness during her menstrual cycle.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 42, 8, 43, 44, 'issue of blood twelve years', 'Connection of Healing Stories', 'Both passages emphasize a woman with an issue of blood for twelve years. They describe her desperate condition and her attempt to seek healing, highlighting her faith in touching Jesus'' garment.', 'parallel', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 40, 9, 20, 22, 'issue of blood twelve years', 'Connection of Healing Stories', 'Both passages emphasize a woman with an issue of blood for twelve years. This connection highlights her faith in touching Jesus'' garment for healing, demonstrating a shared narrative of desperation and restoration.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 3, 15, 19, 20, 'issue of blood', 'Connection of Blood Issues', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a woman having an issue of blood, highlighting the associated ritual impurity. The SOURCE verse details a woman''s condition, while the TARGET passage outlines the implications of such an issue according to the law.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 43, 5, 5, 6, NULL, 'Healing of Long-Term Infirmities', 'Both passages emphasize individuals suffering from long-term ailments, highlighting the theme of healing. The woman in Mark suffered for twelve years, while the man in John had an infirmity for thirty-eight years.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 42, 13, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Women''s Infirmities', 'Both passages emphasize women suffering from long-term ailments. The first woman has an issue of blood for twelve years, while the second woman has a spirit of infirmity for eighteen years.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 5, 25, 44, 4, 22, 22, NULL, 'Healing and Duration of Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of healing after long-term suffering. Both passages refer to individuals who experienced significant health issues for many years before receiving miraculous healing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
