(41, 5, 26, 19, 108, 12, 12, NULL, 'Human Help and Its Limitations', 'Both passages emphasize the ineffectiveness of human assistance in times of trouble. The woman in Mark 5:26 experienced suffering despite seeking help from many physicians, paralleling the plea in Psalms 108:12 for divine aid, highlighting that ''vain is the help of man.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
